<P ID="17"><ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Myrtie</ENAMEX> was born <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Nov. 2, 1933</TIMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Celina</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Tenn.</ENAMEX>, the daughter of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Hattie McAppen</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Clurie Albert Strong</ENAMEX>. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Myrtie</ENAMEX> received her education in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Tennessee</ENAMEX>. In <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1953</TIMEX> she married <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Leonard Shaw</ENAMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Indiana</ENAMEX>. Following their marriage they moved to <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Kentucky</ENAMEX>, then back to <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Indiana</ENAMEX> in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1965</TIMEX>. Her husband, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Leonard</ENAMEX>, died in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1974</TIMEX>. She later moved to Flordia in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1985</TIMEX> before settling in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCATION">Alderwood</ENAMEX> in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1989</TIMEX>. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Myrtie</ENAMEX> enjoyed yard sales, her canine companion, Little Bit, gardening, flowers and spending time with her grandchildren and great-grandchildren.
